At the 67th Republic day celebrations in Yadgir on Tuesday, Minister for Textiles, Ports and district in-charge Baburao Chinchansur unfurled the National Flag at the District Sports Stadium.Remembering the struggles and sacrifices made by national leaders such as Mahatma Gandhi, Subhas Chandra Bose, Vallabhbhai Patel, Moulana Abdul Kalam Azad for Independence, Mr. Chinchansur appealed to the youth to adopt the principles of such leaders to build a strong nation.The Minister also said that India had been recognised as the worldâ€™s biggest democracy as it was following the concepts enunciated in the Constitution.Mr. Chinchansur received a guard of honour by the police, Scouts and Guides and Home Guards during the event.Students from different schools performed cultural programmes.In RaichurIn Raichur, Minister of State for Medical Education Sharanprakash Patil unfurled the National Flag at the Police Parade Grounds.Several cultural programmes were held during the event.